cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with constructing a finite automaton recognizing a set of words from a regular language. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces new regular operators and formulae to compute derivatives, which are relevant to algorithmic design. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper deals with similarity operators, which are relevant to similarity-based learning algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper deals with a generalization of the notion of distance, which is relevant to information theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper deals with regular expressions, which are commonly used in software engineering for pattern matching and text processing.
